PrecisOrder (a) setting apart some 704 hectares of land in Saskatchewan for the use and benefit of the SAULTEAUX BAND as Saulteaux Indian Reserve No. 156C, and (b) consenting to the exercise by SASKATCHEWAN TELECOMMUNICATIONS of its power to take possession of an easement on that reserve, for the purposes of a telecommunications transmission system right-of-way.
